snippet.textDisplay: I’ve watched enough performances of her from when she was 18 to know she never lipsync. There’s a reason why people said Taylor Swift can’t sing. Because when she started she didn’t have enough control, power, or the stamina for live performances. So sometimes she sounded really really good. And sometimes she sounded a bit shaky especially in live tv performances cause of nerves. But she always sound great in her concerts or acoustic performances where she felt most comfortable. Overtime she really work hard to get better. And now that she rarely sound off or shaky people think she lipsync. She never does. She just get better and better with time, experience, and exercise. And this girl rarely cancel shows. Even when she was sick or bad weather. She’ll make it your best rain concert ever. A lot of fans are in raincoats but she performed in rain no cover with wet hair and everything. She’s committed to her job and her fans.
